post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Smoking](https://www.cancer.org/cancer/cancer-causes/tobacco-and-cancer/secondhand-smoke.html) puts the drugs into the air, meaning non-consenting people take the drug as well.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The Federal Government \\(US\\) has no constitutional authority to regulate what citizens choose to put in their bodies. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In countries where "snus" is legal, the boxes has a compartment for spent product. This would disincetivized and lead to higher penalties if possession was illegal. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalisation will at length normalize drug use, which can lead to excess use as with alcohol \\(drinking games, binge drinking\\) which can be far more dangerous when done with hard drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Albert Hofman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albert_Hofmann), the creator of LSD, took LSD for over two decades without any health implications.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The negative repercussions of drug use should be prosecuted on their own merit and context \\(without prosecuting the drug use itself\\).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The fact that legalising drugs would not "end all crime" does not means that it would not damage criminal organizations. It\'s a step in the right direction to reduce their power.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legalized would allow the injured victims \\(or their heirs\\) of fraudulently/irresponsibly cut/marketed drugs to legally and publicly sue the manufacturer/distributor for damages, thereby using market pressures to better assure product/service quality/safety. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If only leaving syringes was punishable, and not use or possession of drugs, they would put in the extra effort to _not_ break the law at all. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Some drugs - hypnotics and barbiturates in particular - are used maliciously as date-rape drugs. Control of these drugs may be preventing rapes from occurring. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This is an argument of the ends justifying the means. The government could generate more income by simply taking everyone's money by force - that doesn't make it a good choice. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing would lead to a better understanding of addiction in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The results can be made evident through legal packaging requirements and health campaigns. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the government cannot take responsibility for a dangerous activity which takes place in society, there is no guarantee anyone else will.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can be used to abuse others or commit crimes.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The syntheses for many illicit, addictive and recreational drugs is already known, there would be high amounts of money spent on R&D for new less addictive drugs. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs such as PCP have caused [grotesque instances](https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/real-life-stories/rapper-killed-girlfriend-chewed-up-11566075) of violence by the user onto other individuals.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Psychosis](https://www.earlypsychosis.ca/pages/curious/concerned-safety) can cause the sufferer to carry out self-harm or, in severe cases, suicide. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Governments manipulate citizens by spreading biased information about drugs and thereby interfering with their choices. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Using a fake ID in a legal establishment implies much more work and risk than just buying from the unregulated black market.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's important to have a standardized quantity of an active substance of controlled quality to prevent overdosing unwanted effects. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Removing support for someone mentally ill comes with costs. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's easier to regulate established companies in a legal market than it is in the black market. Any issue would be with bad regulations, not legalization. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Thousands of people [are killed](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/mexicos-drug-war) annually by drug cartels.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the pursuit of freedom and promotion of liberty are goals of a state, then the laws surrounding drug use are incompatible with freedom and liberty.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The Federal Government \\(US\\) has no constitutional authority to regulate what citizens choose to put in their bodies. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Heroin users](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/what-are-medical-complications-chronic-heroin-use) experience mental disorders, such as depression, insomnia and antisocial personality disorder.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Drug trafficking](https://www.cnbc.com/2013/08/09/Organized-crime:-Worlds-most-lucrative-criminal-activities.html?slide=1) is the most lucrative form of illicit business, worth about $2.1 trillion per year.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It may be difficult to find and employ the right kind of medical professionals who can support the user's needs effectively \\(helping the user in dealing with trauma from their past & their conditioning from childhood\\) I think drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There has been [no scientific consensus](https://newatlas.com/study-effects-ecstasy/10995/) on the long-term effects of ecstasy use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer will benefit all users, while a false sense of safety only applies to a minority. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs may be adulterated despite legalisation, like [alcoholic beverages.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20959682) I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Selling harmful products is a poor long-term business strategy, as can be seen with tobacco companies. It only works as long as there is uncertainty in their harms. When the harms become apparent, people will take measures to stop using it as well as take measures to stop others from using it.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Justifying a ban because it provides people with more autonomy is an inherent contradiction. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking the stigma and secrecy away from drug taking would mean family and friends would notice drug abuse earlier and be able to intervene.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The Netherlands' comparably liberal [drug policy](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) has generated positive outcomes."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing marijuana will increase the risk of accidents on the highways \\(and indeed has in [Washington, Oregon and Colorado](http://fortune.com/2018/10/18/legal-marijuana-car-accidents-study/) where it has been legalized\\) causing harm to others.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a high level of correlation between [poverty](https://borgenproject.org/addiction-poverty-connected/) and substance abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Governments manipulate citizens by spreading biased information about drugs and thereby interfering with their choices. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only a viable strategy for some individuals whom are already close to the legal age, as opposed to a much younger person buying from other young people recruited by the black market.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing marijuana will increase the risk of accidents on the highways \\(and indeed has in [Washington, Oregon and Colorado](http://fortune.com/2018/10/18/legal-marijuana-car-accidents-study/) where it has been legalized\\) causing harm to others.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "That's exactly what we have today. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, there were very few production standards \\(if any\\), meaning the consumer did not know what \\(potentially dangerous\\) conditions the alcohol had been manufactured in \\([pg. 4](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\).'}

This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Marijuana use in the Netherlands has [not increased](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) following decriminalisation; in fact, cannabis consumption is lower compared to countries with stricter legislation such as the UK.'}

But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legal, health institutions can give people valuable information on how much you can take and other health advice on drugs. Now they can't because they would 'support' taking drugs and so also 'support' something illegal. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The decision to use drugs should rest solely with individuals.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although not all people are affected in this way, the risk for psychosis is higher [when regularly consuming cannabis with a high concentration of THC.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2801827/)'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap [substitutes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desomorphine#Toxicity_of_%22krokodil%22) like krokodil cause severe health problems. If drugs were legal and cheaper, substitutes lose popularity.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various governments have already facilitated access to drugs and positive outcomes have come of this.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would enable people to easily manage their own pain medication themselves without the trials and tribulations of doctors and presciptions and all those agonizing hoops you need to jump through along the way.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't necessarily mean drugs should be legalized. Alternatively, we could make alcohol, cigarettes and fast food illegal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs should not be a prerequisite for better education. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
